        "created_at": "2018-04-04T01:38:22.000Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/wine.asp?iWine=2852482\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2015 Domaine Michel Juillot Mercurey 1er Cru Clos Tonnerre</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te Chalonnaise, Mercurey 1er Cru (4/3/2018)</em><br>\nA great value in Burgundy. Has some really nice cherry and floral notes on the nose with dark and deep flavors on its palate. While there is some density on the palate that is less attractive to me, its flavors are true and seemingly pure. Michel Juillot\u2019s wines are routinely overlooked, but there are some very nice surprises. <em><strong>(88 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
